sub_title: PhD student - University of Twente, part of the CATALYST project
summary:
After my BSc at the University of Bologna, I embarked on a new challenge abroad. The University of Twente provided me with a brand new environment full of opportunities. As an MSc student of Industrial Engineering, I developed a deep interest in Lean Manufacturing, Warehousing techniques and Change Management.

Now, I work on the logistics of the future, as a PhD taking part in the CATALYST project.

Beside my work, I am passionate about martial arts (Chinese and European), CrossFit, personal development, psychology and leadership.
